# Normalize line endings to LF on checkout for all text files so JS sources,
# Markdown, YAML, and JSON are byte-identical across Linux, macOS, and Windows.
#
# Without this, git for Windows (core.autocrlf=true by default) checks out text
# files with CRLF line endings. A stray \r in ESM module sources or hook config
# breaks parsing and the Node --test suites that exercise them.
# `text=auto` lets git auto-detect binary files (NUL bytes) and leave them alone;
# `eol=lf` forces LF on both checkin and checkout, overriding autocrlf.
* text=auto eol=lf